And splickem STFU, whoever you are. You make your self look like a total ass, sorry, but its true. You comment about narrowmindness only means that you dislike her becuase she doesn't aggree with you. Happens all the time in real life, why don't you step away from the compture you might under stand...<br>
<br>
On to a few other points...<br>
<br>
Out fitting your MT is a great idea in practice, it really is. I mean you have one BADASS Tank that can take a hella beating and pull out some crazy crap and live. While this is a good thing, there are a few serious draw backs that you should be aware of. <br>
<br>
Once the tank is out fitted with end game gear, then they get lazy and get  "what do I need to come to this raid/log on today" additudes...:( We had this happen in Taltos. We out fitted our MT with Keal armor and then finially was able to get his Light sabers for him and what does he do? Quits not a week later... /boggle Ok so this happened once. /shrug. I have seen this happen many a times actually. <br>
<br>
What happens to your guild while your out fitting your MT, they become bitchy. They start feeling slighted. They start to become resentfull. This is a very delicate thread to walk. Becarefull if you decide to do this and watch for theses signs.<br>
<br>
With that said. Someone mentioned haste items. Well incase you have been living under a rock, there is a WONDERFULL haste item thats doesn't take an act of god to get. Most likely one or two groups can do this. Its in Sirens, and is a 34% haste. 2% lower than COF... NOT BAD... Do your home work and get your tanks from freaken haste items better than an FBSS and stop bichen you can't take tougher mobs down...<br>
<br>
From the guilds I have been in the past, I would say "Hey guys, our tanks NEED this haste belt or this item." and you know what would happen? People would ignore it. We'll that only tells me that they don't give a rats ass about their guild or about having any type of goals...<br>
<br>
