<br>
Most larger guilds go through the same basic maturing process.  Granted, some guilds do it quicker than others.  What was good for guild A 6 months ago is still good for guild B today.<br>
<br>
To state a guild not currently hunting in ToV makes them substandard holds no merit.  I don't know what guild you're in, but before you set foot in ToV, were you substandard?  By your definition, you'd have to say yes.  When other guilds make it to ToV, and your guild has moved on to other areas, will your definition of &quot;good&quot; change, simply because others aren't doing what you're doing? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upalimaxsceleris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palimax Sceleris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/17/02 12:04:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=818.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dear Menn..er Logix</span><hr size=1> It's <br>
