<br>
Ok, where to start...<br>
<br>
With the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Robe Question</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, first, yes, the robe form PoG is very similar to the Thurgadin robe, but inferior (somewhat) to the Skyshrine or Kael robes, but not to the as inferior as an SMR or Froglock Bonecaster.  Your system punishes, rather than rewards, players for personal (non-guild) development.  To take the example to the extreme, since I have a &quot;low Velious&quot; robe, as long as players who contribute half as much to the guild as I contribute, and players who don't attempt to develop their character on non-guild time, all &quot;high Velious&quot; and god-dropped robes will be randomed by players who wear bad robes.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Is there incentive for me to improve my equipment over the guild mean-average?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bonus Crown</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is also suspicious.  Why are epic items different?  Are diamonds held for warrior epics?  The crown is droppable and trades well.  You reward the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> right now</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in every other scenerio, why not in this case?  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Why not sell the item for peridots, or /random it to the people still on Isle 8?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Best Looting Character</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> only brings one question from me.  What if I play my characters (for argument's sake) evenly, two-fisted, or if it's clear that I play my &quot;alt&quot; cleric more than other people's &quot;main&quot; cleric?  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Is my &quot;alt&quot; still destined to loot behind people who do less for the guild than he does?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The 100-1 Shot</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> very</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> interesting.  Why is this somehow different than Vision's system of handling class based items by mutual consensus of the class.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Can you explain the difference between 2 people agreeing on a non-random loot distribution plan and 6 people agreeing on a non-random loot distribution plan?  50 people?  100 people?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Multi-Epic</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is also quite interesting.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> If I organize the next raid on Velkator am I entitled to first pick of loot?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Does this apply to Scout Charissa and Lozidal?  If I see them first, am I entitled to the quest reward or the scale? <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>,
